ENHANCED PROMPT:

## Task: Improve All-Day Availability Slot Management

### Problem Description
When a provider creates all-day availability slots, the system currently treats it as a single 1440-minute slot. This is problematic because:
1. Providers may want to indicate availability for the entire day without creating individual time slots
2. The current implementation doesn't allow providers to specify how many sub-slots should be created within the all-day period
3. There's no intelligent distribution of time across multiple sub-slots

### Desired Solution
Enhance the availability system to:
1. Allow providers to specify the number of sub-slots when creating all-day availability
2. Automatically calculate and distribute time evenly across sub-slots
3. Provide a better user experience for managing all-day availability

### Technical Context
- File: @frontend/src/app/dashboard/components/availability-dialog/availability-dialog.component.ts
- File: @frontend/src/app/dashboard/pages/availability/availability.component.ts
- File: @frontend/src/app/dashboard/services/availability.service.ts
- File: @backend/src/modules/availability/availability.controller.ts
- File: @backend/src/modules/availability/availability.service.ts

### Implementation Approach
1. Research existing availability implementation using @commands/deep-research.md
2. Plan the feature enhancement using @commands/planning-workflow.md
3. Execute the implementation using @commands/execution-guide.md
4. Manage tasks using MCP task management tools

### Technical Considerations
- API enhancement may be required to support the new functionality
- Frontend UI/UX improvements needed for slot configuration
- Backend logic for time distribution across sub-slots
- Database schema considerations for storing sub-slot information
- Validation of user inputs for slot count and duration

### Success Criteria
- Providers can specify number of sub-slots for all-day availability
- System automatically calculates and distributes time evenly
- Existing functionality remains unaffected
- Proper error handling for edge cases
- Comprehensive testing of new features
